Target audience and mission:<br />&#13;
This tour guide was written for social science researchers who are in an early stage of practising research data management. With this tour guide, CESSDA wants to contribute to increased professionalism in data management and to improving the value of research data.<br /><br />&#13;
Overview:<br />&#13;
If you follow the guide, you will travel through the research data lifecycle from planning, organising, documenting, processing, storing and protecting your data to sharing and publishing them. Taking the whole roundtrip will take you approximately 15 hours. You can also just hop on and off.<br /><br />&#13;
During your travels, you will come across the following recurring topics:<br />&#13;
Adapt Your DMP<br />&#13;
European Diversity<br />&#13;
Expert Tips<br />&#13;
Tour Operators<br /><br />&#13;
Current chapters include the following topics:  Plan; Organise &amp; Document; Process; Store; Protect;  Archive &amp; Publish.  Other chapters may be added over time.

